cs.GT, cs.EC, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper deals with game theory and mechanism design, which are typically categorized under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.EC (Economics and Computation). The use of probability distributions and the analysis of equilibria suggest a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), while the modeling of utility functions and decision-making processes may involve artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social networks (cs.SI).
